Document: OpenXRMarkerTracker
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrmarkertracker.rst
Summary: Core methods for retrieving and setting marker data in OpenXR tracking.

- get_marker_data() → Variant (const): Returns current marker data as a Variant. This is a constant method that does not modify the object state.
- set_marker_data(marker_data: Variant) → void: Updates marker data from a Variant input. Accepts any data type compatible with Variant storage.

Key Rule: The get_marker_data method must be called on a valid OpenXR marker instance to retrieve meaningful data.
---CHUNK---
Document: OpenXRMarkerTracker  
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrmarkertracker.rst  
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring and querying marker tracking data in OpenXRMarkerTracker.  

bounds_size (Vector2): The bounds size for this marker. Default: Vector2(0, 0). Set via set_bounds_size(value: Vector2), get via get_bounds_size().  

marker_id (int): The marker ID for this marker, only returned for Aruco and April Tag markers. Default: 0. Set via set_marker_id(value: int), get via get_marker_id(). Note: Use get_marker_data() for QRCode markers.  

marker_type (MarkerType): The type of marker. Default: 0. Set via set_marker_type(value: MarkerType), get via get_marker_type(). MarkerType enum values: 0 (unknown), 1 (Aruco), 2 (April Tag), 3 (QRCode).
---CHUNK---
Document: OpenXRMarkerTracker
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrmarkertracker.rst
Summary: Methods for retrieving and setting marker data associated with QR code markers.

Method: get_marker_data() → Variant
Returns the marker data for this marker. This can return a String or PackedByteArray. Only applicable to QR Code based markers.

Method: set_marker_data(marker_data: Variant) → void
Sets the marker data for this marker.

Note: This should only be set by marker discovery logic.